# Force LF on CI-critical files regardless of a contributor's core.autocrlf.
# GitHub Actions runs on Linux; a CRLF in a `run:` block would append a stray
# \r to every shell command and break the step. The repo blobs are already LF
# (autocrlf=true normalized them); this makes that guarantee explicit.
/.github/**/*.yml   text eol=lf
/.github/**/*.yaml  text eol=lf
/requirements-ci.txt text eol=lf
